// VM test: the SAME multi-data-pool layout as data-pools/plain, but driven by
// the real unified profile (top-level host_profile: arch-data) instead of an
// inline install with hand-written disks. This is the real-prize path for
// issue 12 / ADR 0037: profile_resolve_config → _profile_resolve_host →
// picker_build_assignment slices the VM's 4 × /dev/sdX onto the declared
// groups by disk_count (os_pool none 1, tank0 stripe 1, tank1 mirror 2) in
// declared order — exactly what `install.sh --profile arch-data` produces:
//   /dev/sda → rpool (OS, topology=none, 1 disk)
//   /dev/sdb → tank0 (1-disk stripe)
//   /dev/sdc + /dev/sdd → tank1 (2-disk mirror)
// arch-data declares vm-data, so pool-owners gives the /data pools to that
// user. verify.boot runs the pool verifier; the sentinel fires only when every
// pool imported, every data dataset mounted, every leaf vdev resolves via
// by-id, and each pool is owned by vm-data. Closes issue 08 AC3.
{
  "name": "arch-zfs-test-data-pools-profile",
  "hardware": { "disks": [20, 20, 20, 20], "ram_mb": 4096, "vcpus": 2 },
  "host_profile": "arch-data",
  "verify": {
    "boot":   true,
    "by_id":  true,
    "pools":  ["rpool", "tank0", "tank1"],
    "mounts": ["tank0/data:/data/tank0", "tank1/data:/data/tank1"],
    "owned":  ["/data/tank0:vm-data", "/data/tank1:vm-data"]
  }
}
